a taxing woman ( マルサの女 marusa no onna ) is a 1987 japanese film written and directed by juzo itami .   it won numerous awards , including six major japanese academy awards .   the title character of the film , played by nobuko miyamoto , is a tax investigator for the japanese national tax agency who employs various techniques to catch tax evaders .   the director reportedly was inspired to make the film after he entered a much higher tax bracket after his success with the funeral .   a sequel , a taxing woman 2 , featuring some of the same characters but darker in tone , was released in 1988 .